MPC GENERATING, LLC MARKET-BASED RATE TARIFF
1. Availability. MPC Generating, LLC ("MPC Generating") will make available under this Tariff to any purchaser for resale: (i) electric capacity; (ii) electric energy; and (iii) the ancillary services listed in this Paragraph 1:
Third-Party Provider
Third-party ancillary services: MPC Generating offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity, and ancillary services by MPC Generating, which are (a) subject to the jurisdiction of the Commission, and (b) not made pursuant to another tariff on file with the Commission.
3. Compliance with Commission Regulations. MPC Generating shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning MPC Generating's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes MPC Generating to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits MPC Generating's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning MPC Generating's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
4. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority. In Monroe Power Company, 87 FERC 61,209 (1999) and MPC Generating, LLC, Docket No. ER02-1238 (Apr. 8, 2002) (unpublished letter order), the Commission granted MPC Generating the following waivers and blanket authorization: (i) waiver of Parts 41, 101 and 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15 of the Commission's regulations; (ii) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, except for Sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; and (iii) blanket approval as to Section 204 of the Federal Power Act and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and debt and assumptions of liabilities.
5. Rates. All sales under this Tariff shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and MPC Generating.
6. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions for any sales under this Tariff shall be established by agreement between purchaser and MPC Generating.
7. Seller Category. MPC Generating is a Category 2 Seller in the Southeast region, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a), and a Category 1 Seller in the Central, Northeast, Northwest, Southwest, and Southwest Power Pool regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
8. Effective Date. This Tariff is effective on such date as set by the Commission.
